daily_summary.headline: Exciting Day for Space Enthusiasts: Multiple Launches and Aurora Opportunities

top_events.title: Falcon 9 Block 5 | Starlink Group 17-26 Launch
top_events.description: SpaceX is launching a batch of 25 Starlink satellites to enhance global internet coverage.
top_events.action: Watch the live stream for a glimpse of the future of global internet.

top_events.title: HASTE | That's Not A Knife (DART AE) Launch
top_events.description: Rocket Lab's suborbital launch for hypersonic vehicle testing.
top_events.action: Follow the updates for insights into hypersonic technology.

top_events.title: Aurora Viewing Opportunity
top_events.description: A G1 geomagnetic storm offers a chance to view auroras at high latitudes.
top_events.action: Check the skies if you're at a high latitude.

opportunities.recommendation: Good viewing opportunity for high-latitude observers. Worth checking if you're above 60° latitude and skies are clear.
Possible aurora at high latitudes. Best for northern locations (65°+). Worth checking if conditions are optimal.
